The paper discusses a method for detecting Trojans in deep neural networks, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The method is evaluated on datasets and models from multiple domains, including vision, text, and audio, which suggests that it could also fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV), software engineering (cs.SD), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). However, since the focus of the paper is on Trojan detection, cs.CR is the most likely category, followed by cs.LG and cs.CV.
